The  World Bank  approved a $150
million loan to  China  for energy efficiency improvements in the
eastern Chinese province of Shandong, the bank said in an email
statement.  The loan aims at increasing the use of biomass for power
and heat generation and will include energy efficiency leasing
arrangements, the statement said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
